Basic shortcut keys for Blender

Viewport Navigation:
1.	Middle Mouse Button (MMB) - Rotate the view.
2.	Shift + MMB - Pan the view.
3.	Scroll Wheel - Zoom in and out.


Focus and Centering:
1.	Numpad . (Period) - Focus on the selected object.
2.	Home - Frame all objects in the view.


Object Mode Shortcuts:
1.	G - Move (Grab)
2.	S - Scale
3.	R - Rotate
4.	Shift + D - Duplicate
5.	Alt + D - Linked Duplicate
6.	X or Delete - Delete
7.	Ctrl + J - Join selected objects
8.	Tab - Toggle between Object Mode and Edit Mode
9.	Ctrl + A - Apply transformations (Location, Rotation, Scale)
10.	H - Hide selected object
11.	Alt + H - Unhide all hidden objects
12.	Shift + A - Add a new object (e.g., mesh, light)
13.	Ctrl + Z - Undo
14.	Ctrl + Shift + Z â€“ Redo



Edit Mode Shortcuts:
1.	G - Move (Grab)
2.	S - Scale
3.	R - Rotate
4.	E - Extrude
5.	I - Inset
6.	Ctrl + R - Loop Cut
7.	K - Knife Tool
8.	Ctrl + B - Bevel edges
9.	X or Delete - Delete selected vertices, edges, or faces
10.	A - Select all / Deselect all
11.	B - Box select
12.	C - Circle select
13.	Alt + M - Merge vertices
14.	Shift + Tab - Toggle snapping
15.	F - Fill (Create a face between selected vertices/edges)











Basic shortcut keys for UNITY

Scene Navigation:
1.	F - Focus on the selected object.
2.	Alt + Left Mouse Button (LMB) - Rotate the scene view.
3.	Alt + Right Mouse Button (RMB) - Zoom in/out in the scene view.
4.	Alt + Middle Mouse Button (MMB) - Pan the scene view.
5.	Right Mouse Button + WASD - Flythrough navigation (like FPS controls).


Object Manipulation:
1.	W - Move tool.
2.	E - Rotate tool.
3.	R - Scale tool.
4.	T - Rect tool (for UI).
5.	Q - Toggle between scene view and object manipulation tools.
6.	Ctrl + D - Duplicate selected object(s).
7.	Delete - Delete selected object(s).
8.	Ctrl + Z - Undo.
9.	Ctrl + Shift + Z - Redo.

